HEADWORD: Paramere
<hw>Par"a*mere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>-mere</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
of the symmetrical halves of any one of the radii, or spheromeres, of a
radiate animal, as a starfish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

